    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "512b5e5b_6882c467",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 227,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-22T22:03:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is potentially racy.\n\nupload_thread_ or WebView\u0027s uploader will move the report when checking for pending reports.\n\nMaybe that\u0027s actually okay though. If we\u0027ve already uploaded the report, the uploader can just log the report ID so we don\u0027t need to log the whole minidump. I think it\u0027d be reasonable to reduce these ERRORs to WARNINGs.\n\nupload_thread_ isn\u0027t currently used by Chrome/WebView but moving this block to line 205 could reduce the chances the report is picked up by the Crashpad uploader for other users (it might still periodically poll for reports, even if not triggered here).\n\nIf you really want to make it not racy, I think NewReport needs to provide a FileReaderInterface to the report. As soon as you call FinishedWritingCrashReport(), it becomes available for WebView\u0027s uploader to access.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 216,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 227,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "81a5b55a94ad91219c84d30df30fc5e645f266bf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e53565bf_f802eb21",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 227,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000825
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-22T23:53:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks, since I always saw the report is uploaded after restart, didn\u0027t realized it could be done here.\n\nI moved the code, but hasn\u0027t changed the LOG message yet, my question is if we don\u0027t report the report pending, the report will still be polled? I briefed code it seem that the upload thread only process known_pending_report_uuids_, I may miss some details, what\u0027s the other users you referred to?",
      "parentUuid": "512b5e5b_6882c467",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 216,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 227,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "81a5b55a94ad91219c84d30df30fc5e645f266bf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e28ef5cd_9c7fc541",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 227,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109505
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-23T11:52:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve not looked into this code deeply but replying to Joshua\u0027s comment: if this is a normal condition that can occur due to bad timing, then we ideally should not log anything *at all* in a release build, and certainly not anything that reads \"like an error\" to a human regardless of the log level, because this often confuses app developers greatly.\n\nAlso, I don\u0027t think we can conclude that because the report has been moved by the webview uploader that it\u0027s actually going to be uploaded; IIRC we\u0027re now (or soon) transferring all the crash dumps to the webview crash uploader service (as long as we have user consent), so that they can be shown in the webview developer UI, but we only upload a small sample of the reports after that. (i.e. we moved/are moving the sampling from dump generation time to upload time)\n\nSo, it might be best to come up with a way to avoid the race altogether :|",
      "parentUuid": "e53565bf_f802eb21",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 216,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 227,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "81a5b55a94ad91219c84d30df30fc5e645f266bf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "54c2bcd2_174a9c5d",
        "filename": "handler/linux/crash_report_exception_handler.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 227,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-23T17:42:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it shouldn\u0027t currently be typical. WebView triggers its uploader either at startup or from AwBrowserTerminator after observing a child exit. Crashpad will keep the child alive/attached until HandleExceptionWithBroker() returns, but something else could kill the process before that happens. If there could be other WebView browser processes, threads polling for reports, or anything else that has access to this database, they might remove the report.\n\nBy \"other users\" I mean non-chromium projects using Crashpad. Projects built in chromium will typically use //components/minidump_uploader which has more upload scheduling features for Android, but other projects might be using Crashpad\u0027s built-in uploader.",
      "parentUuid": "e28ef5cd_9c7fc541",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 216,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 227,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "81a5b55a94ad91219c84d30df30fc5e645f266bf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
